cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.HC 

The paper focuses on understanding neural network representations and learning neural networks with interpretable/disentangled middle-layer representations, which is a topic closely related to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the potential benefits of high model interpretability in human-computer communications (cs.HC) and debugging network representations (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of neural networks in learning from few annotations (cs.NE), which further supports the inclusion of this sub-category.
